Operatives of the Kwara State Police Command are on the trail of kidnappers who allegedly abducted a tipper transporter in Ilorin. DAILY POST gathered that the transporter was kidnapped on Tuesday morning along Madi/Oko-Olowo express junction. They have also demanded N30m ransom, sources informed DAILY POST. When contacted, the spokesman of the state police command, Mr. Okasanmi Ajayi, confirmed the report. He said the state police commissioner, Lawal Mohammed Bagega, has directed discreet investigation into the incident.